# Sewar Marine Website

Modern corporate website for Sewar Marine, built with a modern web stack and deployed on Vercel.

## Overview

Sewar Marine is a marine services company providing specialized maritime solutions, offshore support, vessel operations, marine maintenance, and industry-focused services. This project represents the next-generation digital presence of the company, replacing the previous WordPress-based website with a faster, more scalable, and developer-friendly platform.

## Features

* Modern responsive design
* Multi-language support (Arabic & English)
* SEO optimized structure
* High-performance architecture
* Mobile-first user experience
* Fast page loading
* Scalable content management
* Secure deployment pipeline
* Contact and inquiry forms
* Service showcase pages
* Portfolio & project sections

## Technology Stack

* Frontend: Next.js
* Styling: Tailwind CSS
* Hosting: Vercel
* Version Control: GitHub
* AI-Assisted Development: Cloud Code
* Analytics & SEO Optimization

## Project Structure

```bash
/
├── public/
├── src/
│   ├── app/
│   ├── components/
│   ├── sections/
│   ├── lib/
│   └── assets/
├── docs/
└── README.md
```

## Getting Started

### Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/sewar-marine.git
```

### Install Dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

### Run Development Server

```bash
npm run dev
```

### Build Production Version

```bash
npm run build
```

## Deployment

The project is automatically deployed through Vercel.

```bash
npm run build
```

